## Sequential Consistency

All operations appear in **some** sequential order consistent with each thread's program order. Doesn't require real-time ordering.

```
Thread 1: write x=1, then write y=1
Thread 2: read y=1, then read x=0  ← ALLOWED in sequential consistency!

// Thread 2 read y=1 (sees T1's write) but x=0 (before T1's write)
// This is NOT allowed under linearizability
// Sequential: T1's writes happened in order, but globally can be reordered
```

**Used by**: CPU memory models (within certain constraints)
